<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PTM4.4.10">
<l>cīraṇinta maṇimāṭan tikaḻum nāṅkūrt tiruteṟṟi yampalatteṉ ceṅkaṇ mālai</l>
<l>kūraṇinta vēlvalava ṉāli nāṭaṉ koṭimāṭa maṅkaiyarkōṉ kuṟaiya lāḷi</l>
<l>pāraṇinta tolpukaḻāṉ kaliyaṉ coṉṉa pāmālai yivaiyaintu maintum vallār</l>
<l>cīraṇinta vulakattu maṉṉa rākic cēṇvicumpil vāṉavarāyt tikaḻvar tāmē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Those who master these five-and-five [verses] of the garland of song</l>
<l rend="indent">composed by Kaliyaṉ, the one whose ancient fame adorns the world,</l>
<l>Ruler of Kuṟaiyal, king of those of Maṅkai with flag[-bedecked] mansions,</l>
<l rend="indent">the one of Āli Nāṭu, the one skilled with the point-adorned spear,</l>
<l>About my bright-eyed Māl in Tirutteṟṟiyampalam in Nāṅkūr</l>
<l rend="indent">where fine jewel-adorned mansions glitter,</l>
<l>Having become kings of the splendor-adorned world,</l>
<l rend="indent">they will shine as celestials in lofty heaven.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
